commitResults.messageBody:
Programm can receive the command to list out schedule.
They can then print out the cca and test with numberings to the
output of users.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add classes list to be printed
commitResults.messageBody:
List command can now print out classes, ccas and tests which are
padded with numbers.

Checks if the arraylist of strings being returned is expected, when
schedule is empty and schedule has 1 class.

Created command enums to better differentiate which command to
execute.

Lets create a command parser class so that we can have it extract
out the commands from the user ui and then execute them.

Included EmptyListException when there is no class, test or cca. It
will prompt user to add some instead.

Added logging when listing so that we can see the control flow of
the program.

Added assertions in printArrayPaddedNumbers methods to ensure
arguments passed in is not nullable and event array size is not 0.

Catch EmptyListException in here to inform users to add some
instead.

Updated JUnit test for ListSchedule class to check if exception
is thrown if schedules are empty.

Update Expected output for when there is 1 class added.

Lets add an EventManager class that encapsulates the classManager,
testManager and ccaManager. It is also responsible for handling the
listing of all events to user.
